      <section eId="sec_15_2_2">
        <num>15-2-2</num>
        <content>
          <p>Whenever one or more of the Justices of the Supreme Court are unable from providential cause to preside in any case and the parties desire a full bench, it shall be the duty of the remaining Justices to designate a judge or judges of the superior court to preside in the place of the absent Justice or Justices of the Supreme Court.</p>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1888, p. 40, ยง 1; Civil Code 1895, ยง 5506; Civil Code 1910, ยง 6109; Code 1933, ยง 24-4008.)</p>
